Hon Aminu Suleiman, a business Mogul from Kebbi has given a cheque of N100 million to a presidential aspirant, Bola Tinubu.
Aminu, the DG of Tinubu Support Organisation (TSO), revealed that he signed the cheque for Bola Tinubu because he believes in his ability to transform Nigeria if Tinubu is elected president. Suleiman released an official statement on his Twitter which says:” I, Hon. Aminu Suleiman (D.G TSO) will like to officially state that I have signed A Cheque to the tune of 100 million Naira, for the purchase of the Nomination and Expression of interest form for our Leader @officialABAT. God bless.
Tinubu Support Organization also released a public statement following the handing over of the support cheque given to Tinubu stating that the Director-General Tinubu Support Organisation (TSO) Hon. Aminu Suleiman signed an N100m cheque to purchase the APC presidential form for Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu because Asiwaju has helped, raised, and lifted a lot of people and he is a man with a kind heart. They also believe that Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu is the man of every moment and he will transform Nigeria when he becomes the President, there will be economic prosperity and Nigeria would be a better place.
Ever since APC decided to peg its nomination form to #100million, a lot of reactions have been generated left, right, and center across the Nation. Many think it’s an attempt to scare other aspirants aside from Tinubu.


